The paper proposes a continuum theory for unstructured mesh generation in two dimensions, which involves the use of Riemannian manifolds and the Poisson equation. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.MS (Mathematical Software), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), cs.GR (Graphics), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Among these, cs.MS and cs.CG seem to be the most likely categories, as the paper deals with mathematical and computational aspects of mesh generation. The other categories are also possible, as the paper discusses possible applications to graphics and network analysis.
